On the recommendation of the county superintendent, a county board may suspend or dismiss a teacher, principal, supervisor, assistant superintendent, or other professional assistant for:
Immorality;
Misconduct in office, including knowingly failing to report suspected child abuse in violation of § 5-704 of the Family Law Article;
Insubordination;
Incompetency; or
Willful neglect of duty.

The State Board shall adopt regulations to establish standards for effective mentoring, including provisions to ensure that mentors provide mentoring that:
Is focused;
Is systematic;
Is ongoing;
Is of high quality;
Is geared to the needs of each employee being mentored;
Includes observations; and
Includes feedback.
